<br>
My first char is wizzy. <br>
I think all classes are easy to play, but to play well is tough.  Does anyone really play a character to full ability?  Probably not so unfair to say who's toughest, until you can find someone who plays the character to the fullest (plays well.) -  This means every fight you are changing hotkeys, spell slots, not just standing still - auto attack, nuke.. blah blah blah.  <br>
<br>
Let me give some examples on what I mean.<br>
Wiz - yeh we nuke, port, snare, quad - but how many truly use all their spells? Keep themselves buffed all the time? fr, cr, pr, hp/ac, pet, rune, spellshield, DS... changing spell slots in middle of fight, such as debuffs, stuns, rain, ae,... so on.  Think of possibilities combining stuns interrupting mobs cast, debuffing mobs, DS other players, snare, root, raining, ae, concussion, maybe a fade, shadow step.  Endless amounts of combinations mixed with what mobs, what classes in groups, so on ...  Myself I have a set of nukes always memmed, rarely changes depending on raid, group and where, but I am just too lazy to use all my spells, change slots in middle of fight, even though this would be truly most effective and difficult to play. (melee weapons with procs, pets now.. wow goes on.) - bindsight, sense summon, fade whats that?   Aggro? - thats a different topic. <br>
<br>
<br>
Ench - how many use all the buff spells available outside the basic speed, clarity..so on?  Has a boost for almost every stat... Do ench use Umbra often? free rune buff - too long recast?  They have so many buffs... to keep everyone in the group buffed, keep up with mezes, mem blurs, charm, stuns, slow, tash, nuke, ae types, - they just dont have enough slots.  Changing in middle of fight or everytime someone needs buff - too lazy.<br>
<br>
Rog - Just backstab?  Ever try to backstab a mob when soloin - takes some skill.  What about timing mobs casting to move to back and  BS.  How many use poison every fight?  Sure they pickpocket.  Hide to lessen aggro during fight...  Imagine one fight - autoattack, backstab, pickpocket, poison, hide away in middle of fight, move to back during cast.  Maybe switch weapons for proc - snare, buffs, debuff, whatever..<br>
Every fight? - too lazy.  lets just BS and CR.<br>
<br>
<br>
I could go on about each class.. but to &quot;play well&quot; hard to find someone who really plays their class well to the fullest to compare toughness.  Especially with right click items now - only adds to the headache of what a class can do.<br>
<br>
<br>
Toughest class - gotta be necro!!<br>
<br>
Hmm...<br>
pet got it. - if not the best (mage?)<br>
heals got it. - ever see a necro play main healer in group?  ever throw heal use nullify magic on self.. mayb e an exploit not around anymore - havent played one in awhile.<br>
dot got it. - best (stack now? - just heard).<br>
mez got it. - seen it done.<br>
nukes got it.<br>
rez got it.<br>
coth? kinda got it - tricky summon corpse<br>
evac got it - so what at night only? not even sure how it works really just heard.<br>
snare got it.<br>
mana - we all know that (aka manawhore - feed me pls)<br>
buffs - what you dont like DMF?<br>
fear got it.<br>
fd got it.<br>
self mana regen - got it.<br>
life tap got it.<br>
DA got it.<br>
Debuffs got it.<br>
Epic - Ok ya got me, so its not the best - (easiest to get?)<br>
<br>
Hmmm with all these spells someone who plays a necro &quot;well&quot; - which I have only met one person personally.  Would be toughest- because the spells are not the best in the area, so tougher to play and adjust.<br>
<br>
Oh well, just my 2 cps.  Some long reading if your bored.<br>
<br>
Drakkun -<br>
afk: Imbue what? we get that spell?   <br>
